{
  "stem": "23090.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So if this street was to go, after the street supposedly is-- is gone and evacuated, then you send in the police to go through each place to make sure that everyone has-- has, in fact, left and gone with the evacuation.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when that block was gone, we were-- we were-- we were hidden up in her attic and-- We'll have to come back to that--",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I recall there was always-- there were always some-- some outsiders coming in, Jews from other areas.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I never had the-- the-- the privilege or the opportunity to meet them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the conversation was yes, that there were people being coming in from little places.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was like the-- like maybe Lodz was becoming the last place to get everyone together and get them out of there to-- to the next place, which would be the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But yes, there were people that were being-- being really brought all the time from other places.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Since the two major areas of ghettos that we still had was the Warsaw ghetto and the Lodz ghetto, they would use those facilities [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to-- to enable them to go to the next-- to the next step.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my cousin.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My cou-- My cousin, my-- my stepmother's nephew.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were hidden in the-- in the attic.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so when-- she was allowed to stay, because she was a doctor.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was a-- one of those people that was able-- was retained.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when they evacuated her section, the part of her street--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were-- They were-- they were also in the place.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Absolutely, and because our section was already evacuated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were able to stay there for another few days.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
